RACE.FOOTNOTES: TAKE CHARGE SOUSI chased the pacesetter in the two path down the backside, began to close the gap on the frontrunner at the three furlong pole, quickly assumed command at the quarter marker, opened up comfortably in upper stretch and coasted home for the victory. LEGISLATOR trailed three wide at the half mile marker, rallied four wide around horses through the turn, had the winner in his sights at the top of the lane but could not reel him in to pose a threat down the stretch. TOWN'S WARRIOR was unhurried early on the rail to trail the field, took closer order to the pack entering the turn, had to tap on the brakes when behind rivals inside at the three furlong pole, angled outside three deep midpoint on the turn and closed well in the five path to be a clear third in the end. MOON OVER EGBERT led the stalking flight two wide between foes down the backside, was ridden for more with runners on either side at the five sixteenth marker and was one paced finishing to the wire. CADFAEL chased the frontrunner on the rail in the beginning stages, was coaxed for to keep up with three eighths remaining and gave way turning for home. PROUD RONIN set the fractions leaving the chute, continued to dictate the pace angling to the rail into the turn, was collared outside by the winner two furlongs from home and retreated on the fence in mid stretch.

DREAMS AND SCHEMES travelled in the middle of the field under a good hold with four furlongs left to run, picked up the pace between horses midway on the far turn and was five wide offering a good finish in upper stretch battling outside the wire losing out on the place award in the end. HIGH TREASON trailed on the rail in the early going, tried to get more involved three wide at the three furlong pole, made little impact on the final turn and passed tired foes in the stretch. I'M A BOURBON GIRL took the field through the first turn and back straight while setting soft fractions up top, was collared outside by the winner offering no resistance at the quarter pole and tired on the fence at the furlong marker. CRUMLIN BEAST settled in midfield three wide on the first turn, continued that position at the half, when the running started midpoint on the far turn could not quicken with others and gave way in the five path at the top of the stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CRAFTY OAKS broke inwards to begin, recovered to have a good position tracking the top trio four furlongs from the wire, made little gain on the leaders when roused through the turn, split foes in the three path in upper stretch and was full of run rallying in mid stretch to win going away in the end. PIPIT led the field on the rail at the four furlong pole, improved up front on the turn to open up on runners at the top of the lane, began to get leg weary in mid stretch and was caught a few jumps before the wire on the fence by the fast closing winner. THAT GIRL ARTEMUS stalked near the back of the back in the beginning stages, continued to see most of the field entering the stretch, began to find her legs five wide down the lane and closed strongly at the furlong marker to get up for third money. WHY EM SEA AY was bumped at the start to be near the back running down the backstretch, was in tight quarters between horses entering the turn, angled out widest in the six path and finished up evenly for a minor role. MOION was pinched at the start to be near the back in the three path in the early going, put in a good move four wide around foes at the seven sixteenth pole, continued her sustained rally on the turn, loomed five wide in upper stretch and stalled with a sixteenth remaining. MIRAMICHI was away alertly to have a good position down the backstretch, angled to the rail offering an early inside move at the three eighths marker, was in the mix on the fence turning for home and weakened at the sixteenth pole. VILLI OLENTO settled near the rear on the fence down the backside, was steadied on the fence entering the turn, could not regroup to make an impression through the turn and was a non factor to the wire. CALL THE QUESTION broke out at the start, pressed the issue outside at the half, continued to chase the frontrunner through the turn, angled four wide at the top of the stretch and tired at the furlong pole. SWIFT RIVER lost all chance at the start when away poorly, trailed and could not recover to be involved.
